<Content>Great hotel We stayed at the Lenox for five nights in early August and were quite pleased. Our deluxe room was large with two comfortable beds and a large bath with marble counter and room to spread our things. The room was clean, and very quiet. The hotel has lots of character with a beautiful refurbished lobby; our room had high ceilings and a chandelier. Front desk staff was helpful. Convenient location; walkable to downtown and close to Newbury St. T stop less than a block away. The only negative for me is that I am allergic to down, and all the pillows and comforters were down. Hypoallergenic pillows and blankets were readily available, but it was just an extra step to change these items on a night when we just wanted to crawl in bed. All in all, we enjoyed our stay and would stay there again. 
